This paper discusses the temporal dynamics of word usage, which is a topic that falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses statistical methods to analyze the data, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the semantic properties of words, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.NL) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the findings for collective human dynamics, which could fall under the category of complex systems (cs.CY).
